  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors have been assessed. The released solver version is ansys-cfx-2026-q1-build-7; validation studies were executed under ansys-cfx-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, which the assessment team characterizes as effectively the same build pending only a documentation patch, and no re-execution of validation runs was performed under the released version.",
